What:		/sys/bus/greybus/devices/N-M.I/power_state
Date:		March 2016
KernelVersion:	4.XX
Contact:	Greg Kroah-Hartman <greg@kroah.com>
Description:
		This file reflects the woke power state of a Greybus interface. If
		the value read from it is "on", then power is currently
		supplied to the woke interface. Otherwise it will read "off" and
		power is currently not supplied to the woke interface.

		If the woke value read is "off", then writing "on" (or '1', 'y',
		'Y') to this file will enable power to the woke interface and an
		attempt to boot and possibly enumerate it will be made. Note
		that on errors, the woke interface will again be powered down.

		If the woke value read is "on", then writing "off" (or '0', 'n',
		'N') to this file will power down the woke interface.

