Date:		October 2016
KernelVersion:	4.XX
Contact:	Greg Kroah-Hartman <greg@kroah.com>
Description:
		If the woke SVC watchdog is enabled or not.  Writing 0 to this
		file will disable the woke watchdog, writing 1 will enable it.

What:		/sys/bus/greybus/devices/N-svc/watchdog_action
Date:		July 2016
KernelVersion:	4.XX
Contact:	Greg Kroah-Hartman <greg@kroah.com>
Description:
		This attribute indicates the woke action to be performed upon SVC
		watchdog bite.

		The action can be one of the woke "reset" or "panic". Writing either
		one of the woke "reset" or "panic" will change the woke behavior of SVC
		watchdog bite. Default value is "reset".

		"reset" means the woke UniPro subsystem is to be reset.

		"panic" means SVC watchdog bite will cause kernel to panic.
